  Ronke Oshodioke has taken to her social media to pay tribute to late Baba Suwe. The news of the veteran’s death was made known by his son yesterday, Monday 22nd November at age 63. Getting resources from BBC, his death was reported by his child, Adesola Omidina, via online media. Taking to Instagram, Ronke shared a video of them together few years ago while on set. READ ALSO: Actress Ronke Oshodi Oke Remembers Late Daughter After 10 Years The actress said three weeks ago, she posted a clip from a set they both acted as he was easy to work with and it brought back good memories. “About 3 weeks ago I posted a clip from a set we both acted in. You were easy to work with and it brought back good memories.” Ronke said it was really painful for her to hear hos exit as she has planned to post a clip this Thursday just for people to laugh. “Just this week, I got this clip too. It made me laugh and I had planned to post it on Thursday with a funny caption to share the laughter. Somehow I can’t remember what the funny caption was supposed to be, it’s ironic how this video that got me laughing now makes my heart heavy. May angels lead you home, may your path to heaven be well lit. For all the laughter you brought to the world, may you find peace.” See post below:   A post shared by Ibironke Ojo-anthony (@ronkeoshodioke) 